<br>
I'm unlikely to use Resistant at all, even though it's the only discipline I can use at present.  I'd be astonished if any of my saves (usual equipment puts my saves in the 40 to 50 range) were so knife-edged against the mobs I currently fight that an extra +3 would tip me into saving more often.  If in the future I go on encounters where saves become very important (dragon raids for example) I'm going to be loaded out with appropriate save gear.<br>
<br>
If you had the option to add the cumulative bonus onto a single save (eg /disc resistant magic means you get +15 MR for the duration, while /disc resistant would mean you get +3 to all five saves) that would be a lot more worthwhile, and surely hardly unbalancing.  Ho hum <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Fearless, again kinda nice for dragon runs, but if you're optimised for saves, you're likely not going to need it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unluamin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nluamin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/00 9:48:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1958.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious News from the patch</span><hr size=1> Come on, give Verant a break.  I don't think the new disciplines are meant to be used by lvl 50+ pure melee classes.  They are for mid level characters.  My resists are about 25 to 40.  So I am getting a 7.5% to 15% increase in resists which are not bad at all.  Might save me from death.<br>
